 			<p>His seconds were half-supporting him as they helped him through the ropes. He tore free from them, ducked through the ropes unaided, and leaped heavily to the floor, following on their heels as they forced a passage for him down the crowded centre aisle. Leaving the dressing-room for the street, in the entrance to the hall, some young fellow spoke to him.</p>[m
 			<p>“W’y didn’t yuh go in an’ get ’im when yuh ‘ad ’im?” the young fellow asked.</p>[m
 			<p>“Aw, go to hell!” said Tom King, and passed down the steps to the sidewalk.</p>[m
