 			<p>“It is only because of me that you have this house, that you have the food you eat. Your position? Any other man would have been shown the door a year ago⁠—two years ago. I have held you in it. Your salary has been charity. It has been paid out of my pocket. Mary … her dresses … that gown she has on is made over; she wears the discarded dresses of her sisters, of my wife. Charity⁠—do you understand? Your children⁠—they are wearing the discarded clothes of my children, of the children of my neighbours who think the clothes went to some orphan asylum. And it is an orphan asylum … or it soon will be.”</p>[m
